      <h2>Rules & Regulations</h2>

      <!-- Club Mania (1st Semester) -->
      <div class="event">
          <h3>General Rules :-</h3>
          <p>
             All speech time limit range is 4 to 10 minutes per speech for each round. A timekeeper should be present to signal when the speaker is nearing the end of their time.<br>
             There will be team of 2 who will debate on a particular topic. Each team comprises of 3 to 4 members.<br>
             Topic will be provided 30 minutes before.<br>
             The speaker order must be followed <br>
               1st speaker: giving the intro and the argument<br>
               2nd speaker: expand the argument with proper examples<br>
               3rd speaker: summarise the key points and strengthen the team<br>
               Closing speaker: conclude the debate and give the teams main argument
          </p>
          <h3>Specific Guidelines :-</h3>
          <p>
             Topic selection: topic will be provided on the event day. Topic selection will be done by a random chit selection.<br>
             The preparation time is given 45 minutes.Teams or individuals should use this time to organize arguments and strategize.<br>
             Only the team members or the individual participant may be involved in preparing and presenting the arguments. External help (e.g., from coaches or non-team members) is prohibited during the debate.
          </p>
          <h3>Judging Criteria :-</h3>
          <p>
             Judges will assess how logically structured the arguments , relevance of examples used.<br>
             Judges will look for well-organized speeches and clear, concise delivery.<br>
             Effective use of voice (tone, volume, and pace), engagement with the audience, and confident presentation are important.<br>
             Negative marking will be provided if the speaker exceed the time limit.<br>
             Special consideration is done for a rebuttle round.<br>
             The judges will score out of 100 depending up on the structure, rebuttle , example and communication skills.
          </p>
          <h3>Code of Conduct :-</h3>
          <p>
             Speaker should engage peacefully and respectfully rather than personal attacks. Disagreement should be done for the points and arguments not individual.<br>
             Participant should perform a professional behaviour throughout the event including their dress, behaviour, appropriate language.<br>
             Participant should complete with full honesty without misleading arguments.<br>
             Team member should work together efficiently.<br>
             If any sort of confusion or dispute/issue coordinators and the responsible event managers must be contacted.
          </p>
          <h3>Disqualification Condition :-</h3>
          <p>
             Exceeding the time limit<br>
             Interruption between the speeches given by other speaker<br>
             If participants receive external help during the debate, whether from teammates not involved in the round or from non-competitors, this could result in disqualification
          </p>
          
